{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Quick Practice: Japanese→English Speaking Drill (Reverse Translation)",
  "description": "Add a new Quick Practice card 'Reverse Translation' (和文英訳スピーキング) that shows a short Japanese prompt and asks the user to speak the English equivalent aloud. This trains direct L1→L2 output — a proven technique for Japanese learners that the app currently lacks (existing speaking cards prompt in English; existing translation features are read-only, not spoken).\n\nFlow per round (one card session = 5 prompts):\n1. Show Japanese sentence (e.g. 「会議は3時に始まります。」) + a 'Show English' fallback button (hidden by default).\n2. User taps 🎤 to record their spoken English answer using `useSpeechRecognition`.\n3. On stop, compare transcript vs reference English using existing `wordSimilarity` / `classifySimilarity` from `frontend/src/utils/similarity.ts`. Show colored token-level diff (green/yellow/red) and a percent score.\n4. Show the reference English with a 🔊 TTS button (`useSpeechSynthesis`). User can tap 'Try again' or 'Next'.\n5. After 5 prompts, show summary: average match %, count of perfect (≥90%) attempts, and a 'Practice missed ones' button that re-queues low-scoring items.\n\nContent: bundle ~40 curated JP→EN pairs in the component file, tagged by topic (daily / business / travel / restaurant) and difficulty (beginner / intermediate). Difficulty selector picks the pool; 5 prompts are sampled per session. Keep prompts short (5–12 English words) so similarity scoring is meaningful.\n\nFiles:\n- `frontend/src/components/QuickReverseTranslationCard.tsx` (new) — entire UI + bundled prompt list + scoring logic. Mirror the structure/styling of `QuickShadowCard.tsx` and `VocabSpeakRecallMode.tsx`.\n- `frontend/src/components/QuickPracticeHub.tsx` — register the new card (add import, entry in the cards array with title, description, icon, and category 'speaking').\n- `frontend/src/i18n/en.ts` and `frontend/src/i18n/ja.ts` — add minimal strings (card title, description, button labels, summary copy).\n- `frontend/src/__tests__/QuickReverseTranslationCard.test.tsx` (new) — unit tests for: prompt sampling returns 5 unique items, similarity-based scoring classifies a perfect transcript as ≥90, 'Practice missed ones' filters to <70% items, summary stats compute correctly.\n\nFrontend-only, no backend or schema changes. ~5 files, all small. Reuses existing hooks and utils.",
  "files_to_modify": [
