{
  "type": "feature",
  "title": "Add Quick Question Formation card (statement → natural Wh-question)",
  "description": "Add a new Quick Practice card that drills a high-value skill Japanese learners struggle with: forming natural English questions from declarative statements. The user sees a statement plus a target question word (e.g., statement: 'He arrived at the office at 9 a.m.' / target: 'When'), and must speak the corresponding question ('When did he arrive at the office?'). After speaking, show similarity-based feedback against the model answer, allow reveal, and TTS-play the model.\n\nWhy: existing Quick cards cover transformation, register switch, rephrase, connectors, etc., but none specifically drill question inversion / auxiliary placement / Wh-fronting — a top weakness for JP→EN learners and a critical conversational skill (asking follow-up questions in conversation).\n\nImplementation (frontend-only, follows QuickReverseTranslationCard pattern):\n\n1) Create `frontend/src/components/QuickQuestionFormationCard.tsx`:\n   - Curated bank of ~30 prompts: { id, statement, targetWh ('What'|'Where'|'When'|'Why'|'How'|'Who'|'Which'|'How long'|'How often'), modelQuestion, difficulty: 'beginner'|'intermediate' }. Cover present/past/perfect/modals so learners practice auxiliary selection (do/does/did/have/has/will/can).\n   - UI: card title 'Question Formation', difficulty toggle (beginner/intermediate), 'Next' button to shuffle, big statement display with target Wh badge, mic button using `useSpeechRecognition`, transcript display, 'Reveal answer' (Eye/EyeOff like ReverseTranslation), 🔊 button using `useSpeechSynthesis` to play model question.\n   - Feedback: use `wordSimilarity` + `classifySimilarity` from `utils/similarity` to compare normalized transcript vs `modelQuestion`. Show colored badge (great/good/try again) and a small hint when similarity low (e.g., 'Did you start with \"' + targetWh + '\" and use the right auxiliary?').\n   - Track session stats in component state: attempted, great-count, current streak. Persist personal best streak in localStorage under key `quick-question-formation-best-streak`.\n   - Dark-mode styling consistent with other Quick cards (Tailwind classes matching QuickReverseTranslationCard).\n\n2) Register in `frontend/src/components/QuickPracticeHub.tsx`: add an entry to the cards list with a HelpCircle (or MessageCircleQuestion) icon, title 'Question Formation', short description '声に出して自然な質問文を作る練習', and route/render the new component the same way other Quick cards are wired (favorites support comes for free via existing hub logic).\n\n3) Add a unit test `frontend/src/__tests__/QuickQuestionFormationCard.test.tsx` (Vitest + RTL) covering: renders prompt and target Wh, Next button advances to a different prompt, Reveal toggles model answer visibility, similarity classification renders correct badge for a mocked transcript matching the model.\n\nNo backend changes, no schema changes. Bank is fully client-side so no Copilot latency. Estimated ~250 lines for the card + ~50 for the test + 1 small edit to the hub.",
